# .cursorrules
Rules:
  - Always use 4 spaces for indentation
  - Prefer Ruff and Mypy for linting/type checking
  - If user provides incomplete code, ask clarifying questions
  - Code is executed inside Conda environments. Never install packages unless explicitly instructed
  - Provide brief docstrings for every function, including every argument, return and other relevant info
  - Ask questions if you need more information before changing code
  - All Python function definitions must include explicit type annotations for every parameter and for the return type
  - Respect strict type checking (Pyright)
  - Formatting, import sorting, and linting must follow Ruff settings
  - Prefer pathlib over os.path for filesystem paths
  - Use f-strings instead of string concatenation or format()
  - Use dict, list and tuple type definitions instead of Dict, List, Optional
  - Never issue `git commit` or `git push` unless explicitly instructed
